        "version": "2026-07-19T19:12:36.330Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "sayralsabbagh_1950",
        "creatorEnglish": "Ṣabbāgh",
        "creatorArabic": "صبّاغ",
        "sourceId": "alsabbagh_1950",
        "page": "41",
        "commentsEnglish": "Known in Tunis as Ṭabe' al-Dhīl, also Ṭabe' al-Sharqī and Inqilāb al-'irāq.\n\nThe melodies that are close to the melodies of maqām rāst that can be utilised during composition or taqsīm are nahāwand, nawā athar, nikrīz or chahārgāh all on rāst, ṣabā ḥusaynī, ḥijāz nawā and bayyāt nawā. Sometimes after chahārgāh, a transposition of segāh on rāst, then a return to chahārgāh and then to rāst. ",
        "commentsArabic": "",
        "stops": [
          {
            "type": "jins",
            "value": "19",
            "startingNote": "rāst"
          },
          {
            "type": "jins",
