    "suyur": [
      {
        "id": "sayralshawwa_1946",
        "creatorEnglish": "al-Shawwā",
        "creatorArabic": "الشوّا",
        "sourceId": "alshawwa_1946",
        "page": "19",
        "commentsEnglish": "Begins on nawā, then ḥusaynī and 'ajam until muḥayyar ascending and descending, then descends from nawā until yegāh with a touch of qarār ḥijāz before ending on its qarār, yegāh. Therefore it is assumed that the initial ascents and descents are in jins nahāwand nawā as per the construction of the maqām. Also the note qarār ḥijāz does not exist in the list of note names provided by Shawwā in his book.",
        "commentsArabic": "هذا المقام يبدأ من صوت النواه إلى الحسينى والعجم لغاية المحير مراراً صعوداً وهبوطاً ثم يعود من النواه هبوطاً لغاية صوت اليك كاه مع مس عربة قرار الحجاز وينتهى قراره على صوت اليك كاه .",
        "stops": [
