    ],
    "suyur": [
      {
        "id": "sayralshawwa_1946",
        "creatorEnglish": "al-Shawwā, Sāmī",
        "creatorArabic": "",
        "sourceId": "alshawwa_1946",
        "page": "29",
        "commentsEnglish": "There is a discrepancy in Shawwā's representation of this maqām. In the \"rules\" section it says: Starts on ḥijaz to render rāst al-dūgāh then ascends to muḥayyar and during the descent 'ajam is used to render bayyāt dūgāh then kurd on dūgāh then ḥijaz on dūgāh and it ends on 'ushayrān. But in the \"analysis\" section it says: First, jins bayyāt 'ushayrān, second, jins rāst dūgāh, third, bayyāt ḥusaynī. Then ascend to render bayyāt muḥayyar and descend to render rāst nawā, followed by kurdī or ḥijāz dūgāh, then nikrīz rāst and ends with bayyāt 'ushayrān. Rāst dūgāh does not render in most tuning systems, and the note ḥijāz doesn't comply with it's jins. Needs to be researched",
        "commentsArabic": "هذا المقـام يبدأ من عربة الحجاز لعمل مقام راست على صوت الدوكاه ثم صعودا إلى صوت المحير وعند الهبوط تستعمل عربة العجم لعمل بياتى على الدوكاه ثم كوردى على الدوكاه ثم حجاز على الدوكاه أيضا وينتهى قراره حسب شروط سلفه على صوت العشيران .",
        "stops": [
          {
