        "commentsEnglish": "Begins from nawā to segāh, then performs rāst or nahāwand on nawā; after ascending to the jawāb, it descends to the qarār of the maqām, which is segāh. Note: the Turks replace the qarār (segāh) with nīm būselīk.",
