    "commentsEnglish": "Scale deduced by cross-reference (no table in the book) — verify: anchored on the dūgāh qarār (the sayr ends with bayyāt on dūgāh and rāst-on-rāst never occurs in it); rāst-scale degrees are present via the kurdān octave (kurdān = jawāb rāst, awj ascending / ʿajam descending as stated), matching the book's remark that it is close to maqām ḥusaynī.",
