    ],
    "primaryJinsDegree": null,
    "secondaryJinsDegree": null,
    "tertiaryJinsDegree": null,
    "ghammaz": null,
    "suyur": [
      {
        "id": "sayralshawwa_1946",
        "creatorEnglish": "",
        "creatorArabic": "",
        "sourceId": "alshawwa_1946",
        "page": "72",
        "commentsEnglish": "Begins with māhūr — from awj or kurdān descending to nawā — then descends from nawā to dūgāh performing maqām būselīk; its qarār is dūgāh.",
        "commentsArabic": "هذا المقام يبدأ بمقام الماهور أى من صوت الاوج أوصوت الـكردان هبوطاً إلى صوت النواه ثم يهبط من النواه إلى صوت الدوكاه لعمل مقام البوسليك وقراره صوت الدوكاه .",
        "stops": [
          {
            "type": "maqam",
            "value": "55",
            "startingNote": "rāst"
          },
          {
            "type": "note",
            "value": "kurdān"
          },
          {
            "type": "direction",
            "value": "descending"
          },
          {
            "type": "note",
            "value": "nawā"
          },
          {
            "type": "direction",
            "value": "descending"
          },
          {
            "type": "maqam",
            "value": "48",
            "startingNote": "dūgāh"
          },
          {
            "type": "note",
            "value": "dūgāh"
          }
        ],
        "version": "2026-07-19T19:29:39.178Z"
      }
    ],
    "commentsEnglish": "Compound maqām; anchored on the dūgāh qarār stated in the sayr — ascent carries the māhūr degrees above dūgāh (nīm māhūr, kurdān; the rāst tonic exists as kurdān's lower octave), descent is būselīk's. The māhūr entry from awj/kurdān lives in the sayr stops.",
    "commentsArabic": "",
    "sourcePageReferences": [
      {
        "sourceId": "alshawwa_1946",
        "page": "72"
      }
    ],
    "version": "2026-07-19T19:56:31.820Z"
  },
